Cross dresser James Brown has explained why he cut ties with his biological mother. He said his mother has been making attempts to reconnect with him to no avail because he is not interested at all. In a chat with Chude Jideonwo, the socialite explained how his mother rejected and left him with his grandmother. James Brown has always stated he is HIV positive through birth He said that even after reconnecting with his mother, she rejected him. He praised his grandmother who has been his mother figure for him and the new family he created   Actor seeks prayers for abducted father     Suya ‘can give you cancer’, Aproko Doctor claims     JUST IN: Nollywood actor Leo Mezie dies   According to him: “Right now my mom wants to connect but the thing is, I’m not ready. I’ve moved beyond having a mother figure in my life, I don’t need it. “The thing is what people need to know, what they need to care about is that I’m doing well. I’m okay with my life, life is moving on and I’m happy with my life literally. “Every day I’m proud of my family, my new family, the one I created. I don’t want to start touching those wounds which have healed, I’ve actually healed, I’m okay. “But I don’t just feel like it’s the time to start putting myself into that situation because someone that has messed you up before will definitely do it again. “This is the only woman who took me in when I was rejected by my mom back then when I was just two days old. This woman breastfed me, clothed me, and gave me shelter, knowing fully well that I’m just her granddaughter /son. “Back then I thought she was my biological mom for 6 years, even after my biological mother finally surfaced, I was still not accepted. My grandma took me back, loved, and supported me as always. I stayed with my grandma and my great-grandma almost all my life.”